[{"location":"power/#Power-estimation-1","page":"Power","title":"Power estimation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"power/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctpower-1","page":"Power","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctpower","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"power/#","page":"Power","title":"Power","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctpower","category":"page"},{"location":"power/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctpower","page":"Power","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctpower","text":"function ctpower(;param::Symbol, type::Symbol, group::Symbol = :notdef, alpha::Real = 0.05, n::Real = 0, diff::Real = 0, sd::Real = 0, a::Real = 0, b::Real = 0,  k::Real = 1, logscale::Bool = true)::TaskResult\n\nClinical trial power estimation.\n\nparam (Parameter type):\n\n:mean - Means;\n:prop - Proportions;\n:or   - Odd Ratio;\n\ntype (Hypothesis type):\n\n:ea   - Equality;\n:ei   - Equivalence;\n:ns   - Non-Inferiority / Superiority;\n:mcnm - McNemar's Equality test;\n\ngroup (group num):\n\n:one - one sample;\n:two - Two sample;\n\nalpha - Alpha (0 < α < 1)  (default=0.05);\n\nn - Subjects number;\n\ndiff - difference/equivalence margin/non-inferiority/superiority margin;\n\nsd - Standard deviation (σ, for Means only);\n\na -  Group A  (μ₀/p₀) - Test group;\n\nb -  Group B (μ₁/p₁) - Reference group or reference value;\n\nk - Na/Nb (after sample size estimation second group size: Na=k*Nb, only for two sample design) (default=1);\n\nlogscale - diff is log transformed for OR:\n\ntrue  - diff is already in log-scale, no transformation required (default);\nfalse - diff is not in log-scale, will be transformed;\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"power/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.bepower-1","page":"Power","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.bepower","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"power/#","page":"Power","title":"Power","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.bepower","category":"page"},{"location":"power/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.bepower","page":"Power","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.bepower","text":"bepower(;alpha::Real=0.05, theta1::Real=0.8, theta2::Real=1.25, theta0::Real=0.95, cv::Real=0.0, sd::Real=0.0, n::Int=0, design::Symbol=:d2x2, method::Symbol=:owenq, logscale::Bool=true)::TaskResult\n\nBioequivalence power estimation.\n\nalpha - Alpha (0 < α < 1)  (default=0.05);\n\ntheta1 - Lower Level (default=0.8);\n\ntheta2 - Upper level (default=1.25);\n\ntheta0 - T/R Ratio (default=0.95);\n\ncv - coefficient of variation;\n\nn - subject number;\n\nlogscale - theta1, theta2, theta0: if true - make log transformation (default true);\n\ndesign - trial design;\n\n:parallel\n:d2x2 (default)\n:d2x2x4\n:d2x4x4\n:d2x3x3\n:d2x4x2\n:d3x3\n:d3x6x3\n\nmethod - calculating method: Owen's Q Function | NonCentral T, Shifted;\n\n:owenq (default)\n:nct\n:shifted\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"pk/#PK-NCA-1","page":"Pharmakokinetics","title":"PK NCA","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"pk/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.pkimport-1","page":"Pharmakokinetics","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.pkimport","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"pk/#","page":"Pharmakokinetics","title":"Pharmakokinetics","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.pkimport","category":"page"},{"location":"pk/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.pkimport","page":"Pharmakokinetics","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.pkimport","text":"pkimport(data::DataFrame, sort::Array, rule::LimitRule; conc::Symbol, time::Symbol)\n\nPharmacokinetics data import from DataFrame.\n\ndata - sourece DataFrame;\nsort - sorting columns;\nrule - applied LimitRule.\nconc - concentration column;\ntime - time column.\n\n\n\n\n\npkimport(data::DataFrame, sort::Array; time::Symbol, conc::Symbol)\n\nPharmacokinetics data import from DataFrame.\n\ndata - sourece DataFrame;\nsort - sorting columns.\nconc - concentration column;\ntime - time column.\n\n\n\n\n\npkimport(data::DataFrame, sort::Array; time::Symbol, conc::Symbol)\n\nPharmacokinetics data import from DataFrame for one subject.\n\ndata - sourece DataFrame;\nrule - applied LimitRule.\nconc - concentration column;\ntime - time column.\n\n\n\n\n\npkimport(data::DataFrame, sort::Array; time::Symbol, conc::Symbol)\n\nPharmacokinetics data import from DataFrame for one subject.\n\ndata - sourece DataFrame;\nconc - concentration column;\ntime - time column.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"random/#Randomization-1","page":"Randomization","title":"Randomization","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"random/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.randomtable-1","page":"Randomization","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.randomtable","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"random/#","page":"Randomization","title":"Randomization","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.randomtable","category":"page"},{"location":"random/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.randomtable","page":"Randomization","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.randomtable","text":"randomtable(;blocksize = 4, subject = 10, group = 2, ratio = [1,1], grseq = [[\"A\", \"B\"], [\"B\", \"A\"]], seed = 1234)\n\nRandomization list.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#Confidence-Intervals-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence Intervals","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.propci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.propci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.propci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.propci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.propci","text":"propci(x::Int, n::Int; alpha=0.05, method = :default)::ConfInt\n\nConfidence interval for proportion.\n\nComputation methods:\n\n:wilson | :default - Wilson's confidence interval (CI) for a single proportion (wilson score);\n:wilsoncc - Wilson's CI with continuity correction (CC);\n:cp - Clopper-Pearson exact CI;\n:soc - SOC: Second-Order corrected CI;\n:blaker - Blaker exact CI for discrete distributions;\n:arcsine - Arcsine CI;\n:wald - Wald CI without CC;\n:waldcc - Wald CI with CC;\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffpropci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffpropci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffpropci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffpropci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffpropci","text":"diffpropci(x1::Int, n1::Int, x2::Int, n2::Int; alpha::Real = 0.05, method::Symbol = :default)::ConfInt\n\nConfidence interval for proportion difference.\n\nComputation methods:\n\n:nhs - Newcombes Hybrid (wilson) Score interval for the difference of proportions;\n:nhscc - Newcombes Hybrid Score CC;\n:ac - Agresti-Caffo interval for the difference of proportions;\n:mn | :default - Method of Mee 1984 with Miettinen and Nurminen modification;\n:mee | :fm - Mee maximum likelihood method;\n:wald - Wald CI without CC;\n:waldcc - Wald CI with CC;\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrpropci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrpropci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrpropci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrpropci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrpropci","text":"rrpropci(x1::Int, n1::Int, x2::Int, n2::Int; alpha::Real = 0.05, method::Symbol = :default)::ConfInt\n\nConfidence interval for relative risk.\n\nComputation methods:\n\n:mn | :default - Miettinen-Nurminen Score interval;\n:cli | :walters - Crude log interval;\n:li | :katz - Log interval for the risk ratio;\n:mover - Method of variance estimates recovery;\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.orpropci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.orpropci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.orpropci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.orpropci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.orpropci","text":"orpropci(x1::Int, n1::Int, x2::Int, n2::Int; alpha::Real = 0.05, method::Symbol = :default)::ConfInt\n\nConfidence interval for odd ratio.\n\nComputation methods:\n\n:mn - Miettinen-Nurminen CI (deprecated);\n:mn2 | :default - Miettinen-Nurminen CI;\n:woolf - Woolf logit CI;\n:awoolf | :gart - Adjusted Woolf interval (Gart adjusted logit);\n:mover - Method of variance estimates recovery;\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.meanci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.meanci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.meanci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.meanci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.meanci","text":"meanci(m::Real, s::Real, n::Int; alpha::Real = 0.05, method=:default)::ConfInt\n\nConfidence interval for mean.\n\nComputation methods:\n\n:norm - Normal distribution (default);\n:tdist - T Distribution.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffmeanci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffmeanci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffmeanci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffmeanci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffmeanci","text":"diffmeanci(m1::Real, s1::Real, n1::Real, m2::Real, s2::Real, n2::Real; alpha::Real = 0.05, method::Symbol = :default)::ConfInt\n\nConfidence interval for mead difference.\n\n:ev - equal variance (default);\n:uv - unequal variance with Welch-Satterthwaite df correction.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffcmhci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffcmhci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffcmhci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffcmhci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.diffcmhci","text":"diffcmhci(data::DataFrame; a = :a, b = :b, c = :c, d = :d, alpha = 0.05, method = :default)::ConfInt\n\nCochran–Mantel–Haenszel confidence intervals for proportion difference.\n\ndata- dataframe with 4 columns, each line represent 2X2 table\n\na b c d - dataframe table names (number of subjects in 2X2 table):\n\n|         | outcome 1 | outcome 2 | |––––-|–––––-|–––––-| | group 1 |     a     |     b     | | group 2 |     c     |     d     |\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.orcmhci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.orcmhci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.orcmhci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.orcmhci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.orcmhci","text":"orcmhci(data::DataFrame; a = :a, b = :b, c = :c, d = :d, alpha = 0.05, logscale = false)::ConfInt\n\nCochran–Mantel–Haenszel confidence intervals for odd ratio.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrcmhci-1","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrcmhci","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ci/#","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrcmhci","category":"page"},{"location":"ci/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrcmhci","page":"Confidence intervals","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.rrcmhci","text":"rrcmhci(data::DataFrame; a = :a, b = :b, c = :c, d = :d, alpha = 0.05, logscale = false)::ConfInt\n\nCochran–Mantel–Haenszel confidence intervals for risk ratio.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"samplesize/#Sample-size-estimation-1","page":"Sample size","title":"Sample size estimation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"samplesize/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctsamplen-1","page":"Sample size","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctsamplen","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"samplesize/#","page":"Sample size","title":"Sample size","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctsamplen","category":"page"},{"location":"samplesize/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctsamplen","page":"Sample size","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.ctsamplen","text":"ctsamplen(;param::Symbol, type::Symbol, group::Symbol = :notdef, alpha::Real = 0.05, beta::Real = 0.2, diff::Real = 0, sd::Real = 0, a::Real = 0, b::Real = 0, k::Real = 1, logscale::Bool = true)::TaskResult\n\nClinical trial sample size estimation.\n\nparam (Parameter type):\n\n:mean - Means;\n:prop - Proportions;\n:or - Odd Ratio;\n\ntype (Hypothesis type):\n\n:ea - Equality;\n:ei - Equivalencens;\n:ns - Non-Inferiority / Superiority (!one-sided hypothesis!);\n:mcnm - McNemar's Equality test;\n\ngroup (group num):\n\n:one - One sample;\n:two - Two sample, result is for one group, second group size = n * k;\n\nalpha - Alpha (o < α < 1)  (default=0.05);\n\nbeta - Beta (o < β < 1) (default=0.2); power = 1 - β;\n\ndiff - difference/equivalence margin/non-inferiority/superiority margin;\n\nsd - Standard deviation (σ, for Means only);\n\na -  Group A  (μ₀/p₀) - Test group;\n\nb -  Group B (μ₁/p₁) - Reference group or reference value;\n\nk - Na/Nb (after sample size estimation second group size: Na=k*Nb, only for two sample design) (default=1);\n\nlogscale - diff is log transformed for OR:\n\ntrue  - diff is already in log-scale, no transformation required (default);\nfalse - diff is not in log-scale, will be transformed;\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"samplesize/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.besamplen-1","page":"Sample size","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.besamplen","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"samplesize/#","page":"Sample size","title":"Sample size","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.besamplen","category":"page"},{"location":"samplesize/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.besamplen","page":"Sample size","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.besamplen","text":"besamplen(;alpha::Real=0.05, beta::Real=0.2, theta0::Real=0.95, theta1::Real=0.8, theta2::Real=1.25, cv::Real=0.0, sd::Real=0.0, design::Symbol=:d2x2, method::Symbol=:owenq, logscale::Bool=true)::TaskResult\n\nBioequivalence sample size estimation.\n\nalpha - Alpha (o < α < 1)  (default=0.05);\n\nbeta - Beta (o < β < 1) (default=0.2); power = 1 - β;\n\ntheta0 - T/R Ratio (default=0.95);\n\ntheta1 - Lower Level (default=0.8);\n\ntheta2 - Upper level (default=1.25);\n\ncv - coefficient of variation;\n\nlogscale - theta1, theta2, theta0: if true - make log transformation (default true);\n\ndesign - trial design;\n\n:parallel\n:d2x2 (default)\n:d2x2x4\n:d2x4x4\n:d2x3x3\n:d2x4x2\n:d3x3\n:d3x6x3\n\nmethod - calculating method: Owen's Q Function | NonCentral T | Shifted;\n\n:owenq (default)\n:nct\n:shifted\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"export/#Export-1","page":"Export","title":"Export","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"export/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.htmlexport-1","page":"Export","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.htmlexport","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"export/#","page":"Export","title":"Export","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.htmlexport","category":"page"},{"location":"export/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.htmlexport","page":"Export","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.htmlexport","text":"htmlexport(data::DataFrame; io::IO = stdout; sort = NaN, rspan=:all, title=\"Title\", dict::Union{Symbol, Dict} = :undef)\n\nHTLM export for DataFrame.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"nca/#NCA-1","page":"NCA","title":"NCA","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"nca/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.nca!-1","page":"NCA","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.nca!","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"nca/#","page":"NCA","title":"NCA","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.nca!","category":"page"},{"location":"nca/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.nca!","page":"NCA","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.nca!","text":"nca!(data::PKSubject; calcm = :lint, verbose = false, io::IO = stdout)\n\nPharmacokinetics non-compartment analysis for one PK subject.\n\ncalcm - calculation method;\n\n:lint  - Linear trapezoidal everywhere;\n:logt  - Log-trapezoidat rule after Tmax if c₁ > 0 and c₂ > 0, else Linear trapezoidal used;\n:luld  - Linear Up - Log Down everywhere if c₁ > c₂ > 0, else Linear trapezoidal used;\n:luldt - Linear Up - Log Down  after Tmax if c₁ > c₂ > 0, else Linear trapezoidal used;\n\nverbose - print to out stream if \"true\";\n\ntrue;\nfalse.\n\nio - out stream (stdout by default)\n\n\n\n\n\nnca!(data::DataSet{PKSubject}; calcm = :lint, verbose = false, io::IO = stdout)\n\nPharmacokinetics non-compartment analysis for PK subjects set.\n\ncalcm - calculation method;\n\n:lint  - Linear trapezoidal everywhere;\n:logt  - Log-trapezoidat rule after Tmax if c₁ > 0 and c₂ > 0, else Linear trapezoidal used;\n:luld  - Linear Up - Log Down everywhere if c₁ > c₂ > 0, else Linear trapezoidal used;\n:luldt - Linear Up - Log Down  after Tmax if c₁ > c₂ > 0, else Linear trapezoidal used;\n\nverbose - print to out stream if \"true\";\n\ntrue;\nfalse.\n\nio - out stream (stdout by default)\n\n\n\n\n\nnca!(data::PDSubject; verbose = false, io::IO = stdout)::PKPDProfile{PDSubject}\n\nPharmacodynamics non-compartment analysis for one PD subject.\n\n\n\n\n\nnca!(data::PDSubject; verbose = false, io::IO = stdout)::PKPDProfile{PDSubject}\n\nPharmacodynamics non-compartment analysis for PD subjects set.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"examples/#Confidence-intervals:-1","page":"Examples","title":"Confidence intervals:","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"propci(81, 263, alpha=0.05, method=:wilson)\n\ndiffpropci(7, 34, 1, 34; alpha=0.05, method=:nhs)\n\norpropci(2, 14, 1, 11; alpha=0.05, method=:woolf)\n\nrrpropci(2, 14, 1, 11; alpha=0.05)\n\ndiffmeanci(30, 10, 30, 40, 12, 35, alpha=0.05, method=:ev)\n","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Sample-size-1","page":"Examples","title":"Sample size","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#Equivalence-for-two-means-1","page":"Examples","title":"Equivalence for two means","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"ctsamplen(param=:mean, type=:ei, group=:two, diff=0.3, sd=1, a=0.3, b=0.5)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#One-proportion-equality-1","page":"Examples","title":"One proportion equality","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"ctsamplen(param=:prop, type=:ea, group=:one, a=0.3, b=0.5)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Odd-ratio-non-inferiority-1","page":"Examples","title":"Odd ratio non-inferiority","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"ctsamplen(param=:or, type=:ns, diff=-0.1, a=0.3, b=0.5, k=2)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Odd-ratio-equality-1","page":"Examples","title":"Odd ratio equality","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"ctsamplen(param=:or, type=:ea, a=0.3, b=0.5, k=2)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Bioequivalence-1","page":"Examples","title":"Bioequivalence","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"besamplen(alpha=0.05,  theta1=0.8, theta2=1.25, theta0=0.95, cv=0.15, method=:owenq)\n\nbesamplen(cv=0.20, method=:nct)\n\nbesamplen(cv=0.347, design=:parallel)\n\nbesamplen(cv=0.40)\n\nbesamplen(cv=0.347, design=:d2x2x4, method=:nct)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"#Power","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Equality-for-one-mean-1","page":"Examples","title":"Equality for one mean","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"ctpower(param=:mean, type=:ea, group=:one, a=1.5, b=2, sd=1,n=32, alpha=0.05)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Bioequivalence-2","page":"Examples","title":"Bioequivalence","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"#Bioequivalence power for 2x2 design, default method - OwensQ\nbepower(alpha=0.05, logscale=true, theta1=0.8, theta2=1.25, theta0=0.95, cv=0.2, n=20, design=:d2x2, method=:owenq)\n\n#The same\nbepower(alpha=0.05, cv=0.2, n=20, design=:d2x2)\n\n#Bioequivalence power for cv 14%, 21 subjects, default OwensQ method, logscale false\nbepower(alpha=0.1, logscale=false, theta1=-0.1, theta2=0.1, theta0=0, cv=0.14, n=21)\n\n#Bioequivalence power for cv 14%, 21 subjects, shifted method, logscale false\nbepower(alpha=0.1, logscale=false, theta1=-0.1, theta2=0.1, theta0=0, cv=0.14, n=21, method=:shifted)\n\n#Simple notations\nbepower(cv=0.4, n=35, design=:d2x4x4)\nbepower(cv=0.14, n=21)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Utilities-1","page":"Examples","title":"Utilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#CV-from-CI-1","page":"Examples","title":"CV from CI","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"cvfromci(;alpha = 0.05, theta1 = 0.9, theta2 = 1.25, n=30, design=:d2x2x4)","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/#Polled-CV-1","page":"Examples","title":"Polled CV","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/#","page":"Examples","title":"Examples","text":"data = DataFrame(cv = Float64[], df = Int[])\npush!(data, (0.12, 12))\npush!(data, (0.2, 20))\npush!(data, (0.25, 30))\npooledcv(data; cv=:cv, df=:df, alpha=0.05, returncv=true)","category":"page"},{"location":"pd/#PD-NCA-1","page":"Pharmacodynamics","title":"PD NCA","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"pd/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.pdimport-1","page":"Pharmacodynamics","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.pdimport","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"pd/#","page":"Pharmacodynamics","title":"Pharmacodynamics","text":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.pdimport","category":"page"},{"location":"pd/#ClinicalTrialUtilities.pdimport","page":"Pharmacodynamics","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities.pdimport","text":"pdimport(data::DataFrame, sort::Array; resp::Symbol, time::Symbol, bl::Real = 0, th::Real = NaN)\n\nPharmacodynamics data import from DataFrame.\n\ndata - sourece DataFrame;\nsort - sorting columns;\nresp - responce column;\ntime - time column\nbl - baseline;\nth - treashold.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ClinicalTrialUtilities-1","page":"Home","title":"ClinicalTrialUtilities","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"VERSION 0.2.0 INCOMATIBLE WITH 0.1.x","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Clinical trial related calculation: descriptive statistics, power and sample size calculation, power simulations, confidence interval, pharmacokinetics/pharmacodynamics parameters calculation.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"(Image: Build Status) (Image: Build status) (Image: codecov) (Image: Coverage Status) (Image: Latest docs)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Description-1","page":"Home","title":"Description","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The package is designed to perform calculations related to the planning and analysis of the results of clinical trials. The package includes the basic functions described below, as well as a few modules to perform specific calculations.","category":"page"},{"location":"#a-name\"Installation\"Installation/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"Installation\">Installation</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg; Pkg.add(\"ClinicalTrialUtilities\");","category":"page"},{"location":"#a-name\"Usage\"Usage/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"Usage\">Usage</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"NB! Hypothesis types:","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":":ea - Equality: two-sided;\n:ei - Equivalencens: two one-sided hypothesis;\n:ns - Non-Inferiority / Superiority: one-sided hypothesis, for some cases you should use two-sided hypothesis for  Non-Inferiority/Superiority, you can use alpha/2 for this;","category":"page"},{"location":"#a-name\"descriptives\"descriptives/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"descriptives\">descriptives</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Descriptive statistics.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"descriptives(data::DataFrame; sort = NaN, vars = NaN, stats = [:n, :mean, :sd, :sem, :uq, :median, :lq])::DataFrame","category":"page"},{"location":"#a-name\"ci2cv\"ci2cv/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"ci2cv\">ci2cv</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Take CV from known CI and subject number.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"cvfromci(;alpha = 0.05, theta1 = 0.8, theta2 = 1.25, n, design=:d2x2, mso=false, cvms=false)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"alpha - Alpha (o < alpha < 1)  (default=0.05);","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"beta - Beta (o < beta < 1) (default=0.2); power = 1 - beta;","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"theta1 - Lower Level (default=0.8);","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"theta2 - Upper level (default=1.25);","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"n - subject n;","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"design - trial design;","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":":parallel\n:d2x2 (default)\n:d2x2x4\n:d2x4x4\n:d2x3x3\n:d2x4x2\n:d3x3\n:d3x6x3","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"mso","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Calculate MS only","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"false(default)\ntrue","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"cvms","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Calculate CV and MS","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"false(default)\ntrue","category":"page"},{"location":"#a-name\"pooledCV\"pooledCV/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"pooledCV\">pooledCV</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Get pooled CV from multiple sources.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"pooledcv(data::DataFrame; cv=:cv, df=:df, alpha=0.05, returncv=true)::ConfInt","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"data::DataFrame - Dataframe with CV data","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"cv::Symbol - CV column in dataframe","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"df::Symbol - DF column in dataframe","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"alpha - Alpha for var/cv confidence interval.","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"returncv - Return CV or var:","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"true  - return cv\nfalse - return var","category":"page"},{"location":"#-1","page":"Home","title":"","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#a-name\"Examples\"Examples/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"Examples\">Examples</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"#Sample size for one proportion equality\nctsamplen(param=:prop, type=:ea, group=:one, a=0.3, b=0.5)\n#Equivalence for two means\nctsamplen(param=:mean, type=:ei, group=:two, diff=0.3, sd=1, a=0.3, b=0.5)\n#Odd ratio non-inferiority\nctsamplen(param=:or, type=:ns, diff=-0.1, a=0.3, b=0.5, k=2)\n#Odd ratio equality\nctsamplen(param=:or, type=:ea, a=0.3, b=0.5, k=2)\n\n#Power\nctpower(param=:mean, type=:ea, group=:one, a=1.5, b=2, sd=1,n=32, alpha=0.05)\n\n#Bioequivalence sample size\nbesamplen(alpha=0.05,  theta1=0.8, theta2=1.25, theta0=0.95, cv=0.15, method=:owenq)\nbesamplen(cv=0.20, method=:nct)\nbesamplen(cv=0.347, design=:parallel)\nbesamplen(cv=0.40)\nbesamplen(cv=0.347, design=:d2x2x4, method=:nct)\n\n#Bioequivalence power for 2x2 design, default method - OwensQ\nbepower(alpha=0.05, logscale=true, theta1=0.8, theta2=1.25, theta0=0.95, cv=0.2, n=20, design=:d2x2, method=:owenq)\n#Same\nbepower(alpha=0.05, cv=0.2, n=20, design=:d2x2)\n#Bioequivalence power for cv 14%, 21 subjects, default OwensQ method, logscale false\nbepower(alpha=0.1, logscale=false, theta1=-0.1, theta2=0.1, theta0=0, cv=0.14, n=21)\n#Bioequivalence power for cv 14%, 21 subjects, shifted method, logscale false\nbepower(alpha=0.1, logscale=false, theta1=-0.1, theta2=0.1, theta0=0, cv=0.14, n=21, method=:shifted)\n#Simple notations\nbepower(cv=0.4, n=35, design=:d2x4x4)\nbepower(cv=0.14, n=21)\n\n#CV from CI\ncvfromci(;alpha = 0.05, theta1 = 0.9, theta2 = 1.25, n=30, design=:d2x2x4)\n\n#Polled CV\ndata = DataFrame(cv = Float64[], df = Int[])\npush!(data, (0.12, 12))\npush!(data, (0.2, 20))\npush!(data, (0.25, 30))\npooledcv(data; cv=:cv, df=:df, alpha=0.05, returncv=true)\n","category":"page"},{"location":"#a-name\"Copyrights\"Copyrights/a-1","page":"Home","title":"<a name=\"Copyrights\">Copyrights</a>","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Clinical Trial Utilities","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Copyright © 2019 Vladimir Arnautov aka PharmCat (mail@pharmcat.net)","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"If you want to check and get R code for power/sample size estimation, you can find examples here: http://powerandsamplesize.com/Calculators/","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#Sample-size-/-power-1","page":"References","title":"Sample size / power","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"OwensQ/PowerTOST functions rewritten from https://github.com/Detlew/PowerTOST by Detlew Labes, Helmut Schuetz, Benjamin Lang","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Calculation based on Chow S, Shao J, Wang H. 2008. Sample Size Calculations in Clinical Research. 2nd Ed. Chapman & Hall/CRC Biostatistics Series.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Connor R. J. 1987. Sample size for testing differences in proportions for the paired-sample design. Biometrics 43(1):207-211. page 209.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Phillips KF.Power of the Two One-Sided Tests Procedure in BioequivalenceJ Pharmacokin Biopharm. 1990;18(2):137–44. doi: 10.1007/BF01063556","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Diletti D, Hauschke D, Steinijans VW.Sample Size Determination for Bioequivalence Assessment by Means of Confidence IntervalsInt J Clin Pharmacol Ther Toxicol. 1991;29(1):1–8.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Owen, D B (1965) \"A Special Case of a Bivariate Non-central t-Distribution\" Biometrika Vol. 52, pp.437-446.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"FORTRAN code by J. Burkhardt, license GNU LGPL","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"D.B. Owen \"Tables for computing bivariate normal Probabilities\" The Annals of Mathematical Statistics, Vol. 27 (4) Dec. 1956, pp. 1075-1090","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"matlab code  by J. Burkhardt license GNU LGPL","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#Confidence-intervals-1","page":"References","title":"Confidence intervals","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Wilson, E.B. (1927) Probable inference, the law of succession, and statistical inference. J. Amer. Stat. Assoc22, 209–212.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Clopper, C. and Pearson, E.S. (1934) The use of confidence or fiducial limits illustrated in the case of the binomial. Biometrika 26, 404–413.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Blaker, H. (2000). Confidence curves and improved exact confidence intervals for discrete distributions. Canadian Journal of Statistics28 (4), 783–798.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"T. Tony Cai One-sided confidence intervals in discrete distributions. doi:10.1016/j.jspi.2004.01.00.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Newcombe, R. G. (1998) Two-sided confidence intervals for the single proportion: comparison of seven methods. Statistics in Medicine. 17 (8): 857–872. doi:10.1002/(SICI)1097-0258(19980430)17:8<857::AID-SIM777>3.0.CO;2-E. PMID 9595616.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Miettinen O. S., Nurminen M. (1985) Comparative analysis of two rates. Statistics in Medicine4,213–226","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Lawson, R (2005):Smallsample confidence intervals for the odds ratio.  Communication in Statistics Simulation andComputation, 33, 1095-1113.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Woolf, B. (1955). On estimating the relation between blood group and disease. Annals of human genetics, 19(4):251-253.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Gart, JJand Nam, J (1988): Approximate interval estimation of the ratio of binomial parameters: Areview and corrections for skewness. Biometrics 44, 323-338.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Donner, A. and Zou, G. (2012). Closed-form confidence intervals for functions of the normal mean and standard deviation. Statistical Methods in Medical Research, 21(4):347-359.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Newcombe RG (1998): Interval Estimation for the Difference Between Independent Proportions: Comparison of Eleven Methods. Statistics in Medicine 17, 873-890.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Agresti A, Caffo B., “Simple and effective confidence intervals for proportions and differences of proportions result from adding two successes and two failures”, American Statistician 54: 280–288 (2000)","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Mee RW (1984) Confidence bounds for the difference between two probabilities,Biometrics40:1175-1176","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Rothman, K. J., Greenland, S., & Lash, T. L. (2008). Modern epidemiology (3rd ed.). Philadelphia: Lippincott Williams & Wilkins.","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#Interestin-R-packages-1","page":"References","title":"Interestin R packages","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"PowerTOST by by Detlew Labes, Helmut Schuetz, Benjamin Lang  https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/PowerTOST/","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"PropCIs by Ralph Scherer https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/PropCIs/index.html","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"pairwiseCI by Frank Schaarschmidt, Daniel Gerhard  https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=pairwiseCI","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"binGroup by Boan Zhang, Christopher Bilder, Brad Biggerstaff, Frank Schaarschmidt Brianna Hitt https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=binGroup","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"proportion by M.Subbiah, V.Rajeswaran https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=proportion","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"binom by Sundar Dorai-Raj https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=binom","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"DescTools https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=DescTools","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"ORCI by Libo Sun https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=ORCI","category":"page"},{"location":"ref/#","page":"References","title":"References","text":"metafor by Wolfgang Viechtbauer https://cran.r-project.org/package=metafor","category":"page"}]
